    • Constructor Detail

      • DependenceConstraint

        public DependenceConstraint(List<Task> previousTasks)
        The DependenceConstraint function is used to determine if a task can be scheduled. It checks the previous tasks in the list and determines if they have been completed or not. If all of them are complete, then it returns true, otherwise it returns false.
        Parameters:
        previousTasks - Store the list of tasks that must be completed before the current task can begin
